This paper deals with aggregate-join queries, which are commonly studied in the database community (cs.DB). The paper also introduces extensions to generalized hypertree decompositions (GHDs), which are a data structure commonly used in query optimization and processing (cs.DS). The paper presents runtime guarantees and optimizations, which are topics of interest in theoretical computer science (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses efficient methods for finding approximately optimal GHDs, which is a topic in data mining (cs.DM).
